-- Cowen Says Ireland's Government Will Dissolve After Passing Next Budget
-- B y   S i m o n e   M e i e r
-- 2010-11-22T19:17:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/cowen-says-ireland-s-government-will-dissolve-after-passing-next-budget.html
Irish Prime Minister Brian Cowen
said the government will resign after passing the country’s
budget.   “The government will publish its four-year plan next
Wednesday, it will continue negotiations” with the European
Union and the International Monetary Fund, Cowen said at a press
conference in Dublin today. “It’s my intention, to seek a
dissolution” of the government.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Simone Meier at 
 smeier@bloomberg.net  